reviewText: I don't know why people want to do this to their fans... It's too expensive for what you're getting... a few videos. There's a D12 song for promotional purposes and a worthless little tour of Eminem's house you'll never watch twice. The best part was the making of 'Stan'. Could've included a concert performance or interviews. 'Buyer Beware'

reviewText: This DVD's a must own for Eminem fans.All the... videos are here;The Real Slim Shady,Stan,The Way I Am,My Name Is,Role Model, Guilty Consience & Just Don't Give a.... I like 'Guilty Consience' the best.Even though it's the clean version of the song,the video with Em and Dre is excellent. The DVD itself has nicely designed menus and the bonus footage includes the Blair Witch spoof 'The Mathers Home' and the making of the Stan video.It's a bit brief at about eight minutes but it's still a worthwhile look behind the scenes and it also features interviews with Em,Dr.Dre,Dido & Devon Sawa(Stan). It would be cool if Eminem's TRL MTV special was included on the bonus features and too bad the DVD didn't come out later,then it could've included D12's superb 'Purple Hills' video.Still,Eminem fans can't go far wrong with this DVD.The Up In Smoke Tour DVD is also worth checking out.
summary: Eminem makes the best music videos

reviewText: I am a fan of Marshall Mathers (I refuse to call him by Eminem - I think that whole "call me by my nickname 'cause I'm famous" thing is retarded...hello?-P. Diddy, Puff Daddy, Mase, Ol' Dirty Bastard?).  I like his music, even though I don't support all of the things he says in the songs.  Music is entertainment...period.  I don't care if he really is prejudiced, the music is great.  The DVD was weak for the...[money] I paid for it.  It has less music than a regular CD, but costs more - that's not right.  The videos are fantastic.  Especially 'Stan.'  But it really needed a lot more footage to be worth my money.
summary: Not enough bang for your buck

reviewText: So, this is something like every Eminem videoclip from Slim Shady LP and Marshall Mathers LP. The videoclips are mostly good, but I was expecting something more than that... Anyways, these are the videoclips presented in this DVD:- My Name Is: One of the funniest, features Marilyn Manson. This videoclip, as Eminem said himself, was just him trying to show who he was (just like Snoop Dogg has done in the "My Name Is" song). Lyrics have been changed in some parts to fit the censorship rules.- Guilty Conscience: It does have a very different camera move (something like the ones from Matrix movies), very nice indeed. This videoclip features well-known rapper Dr Dre. This clip is about the devil and the angel who live in eveyone's head. Eminem is the devil and Dre is the angel in the clip. Lyrics have been changed too.- Role Model: This is one of the best, if you ask me. It doesn't features anyone, but there is a cartoon part in the middle of the videoclip. One of the funniest too. The lyrics have drastically changed from the LP version to fit the censorship, since this song contains really explicit content in some parts. But it's still very worth to watch!- Just Don't Give A F*ck: This is a black & white, low budget videoclip. The song is very fine, but the video is a little boring, it doesn't have funny parts like the others.- The Real Slim Shady: Well, you all know this videoclip, who features D12. It's really funny (remember the "my bum is on your lips" part?), both the lyrics and the video. Very worthy.- Stan: I think this is the most well-produced videoclip Eminem has ever done. It really looks like a movie. Features singer Dido and actor Davon Sawa from Final Destination. Really nice, really worthy!- The Way I Am: Best lyrics, without a doubt. The videoclip is angry just like the song, but there's no big deal about this one, even though it is good.There are two extras in the DVD, and here they are:- The Making Of Stan: A making-of for the videoclip Stan. It's very nice, really goes into the backstage parts, with little interviews with the guys who have made the videoclips, actors and everything.- The Mathers' Home: Eminem Meets Blair Witch Project. What? Weird? Yes! Some guys enter Eminem's childhood home and they find something very strange in there... It's just a dumb little movie.There is that little "Explicit Content" label in the cover, and you all know why that is that way. Some violence in the clips, language, but no big thing.Overall, it is a fine DVD, it's cool to have all these videos in 5.1 sound. But if you're not an Eminem fan, just forget it. Prefer something like Up In Smoke World Tour if you're not really into Eminem. But if you are, give it a try, this DVD is not bad.
